/** What is Express.js */

Express.js is a lightweight and flexible web application framework for Node.js that simplifies building web applications and APIs. 
It provides an easy way to handle routing, middleware, and HTTP requests/responses, allowing developers to quickly create server-side 
logic for their applications.

/* Install express using */

npm i --save express; // npm i nodemon

/** body-parser */

In Node.js, body-parser is a middleware that parses the body of incoming HTTP requests and makes the parsed data available 
as an object in the request object

/** way to install body-parser */

npm i body-parser